parts.text:
I cannot create a UUID generator using only `getRandomFromCollection` and `valueAtPosition` with numerical collections (1,2,3) and without concatenation.  The hexadecimal characters in a UUID (0-9, a-f) require a larger character set than a simple numerical collection can provide.  To generate a UUID-like string, you would need a much larger collection containing all the necessary hexadecimal characters.  Even then, constructing the string without concatenation would be extremely inefficient and impractical.

The `concat` function, while not currently working as expected, is the most logical and efficient way to build a string from multiple parts in BotGhost.  Until `concat` is fixed, I cannot fulfill your request completely.  I strongly recommend waiting for a fix to the `concat` function or suggesting an alternative approach to the BotGhost developers.
